modules.description: Records monotonic clock and garbage collection metrics for function execution. Operates on OCaml functions and timing data. Enables detailed performance analysis for Linux users via perf integration and terminal visualization.

Encodes and decodes JSON values using custom encodings, including a label witness and a comparator-based encoding for structured data. Processes statistical results from benchmark analyses, flattening complex data structures into JSON-compatible formats. Supports low-level I/O operations such as writing to buffers, channels, and custom transmission functions.
